the LGBTQ+ icon\", \"from\": 380, \"to\": 395}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony's wake\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Source: AP Photo/Tsvangirayi Mukwazhi, File) BLESSINGS: Archbishop Jason Gordon blesses the congregation yesterday during Easter Mass at the Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception, Port of Spain.\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 498, \"end\": 508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9997825331172286, \"rank\": 0.00015775884006074653, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 509, \"end\": 514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"score\": 0.9998079060316184, \"rank\": 0.00019213024792555825, \"text\": \"Jason\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\"}, {\"begin\": 515, \"end\": 521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.9999993142889785, \"rank\": 4.651687596632641e-07, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\"}, {\"begin\": 631, \"end\": 636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9667833390156566, \"rank\": 0.029435134831483856, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"(Source\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"File\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 484}, {\"ngram\": \"the congregation\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"Easter Mass\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"the Cathedral\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 591}, {\"ngram\": \"the Immaculate Conception\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 620}, {\"ngram\": \"Port\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 626}]}, {\"sentence\": \"-Photo: JERMAINE CRUICKSHANK ARCHBISHOP Jason Gordon has said that today's culture appears to be 'against' Christian tradition, as he deemed last Friday's opening ceremony of the 2024 Olympic Games to be a 'parody' of Jesus Christ's Last Supper.\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"score\": 0.9998079060316184, \"rank\": 0.00019213024792555825, \"text\": \"Jason\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason\"}, {\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.9999993142889785, \"rank\": 4.651687596632641e-07, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\"}, {\"begin\": 747, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9991403755832793, \"rank\": 0.0008603640067023825, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 858, \"end\": 870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999894057511, \"rank\": 1.0594409148067646e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"today's culture\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"last Friday's opening ceremony\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 810}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 836}, {\"ngram\": \"a 'parody\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 852}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Archbishop joined other local and international religious leaders in criticising the opening ceremony of the world's mostanticipated multi-sporting event, which some claim was a mockery of Christianity and a declaration of war on Christian values.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 1138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 891, \"end\": 901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9997825331172286, \"rank\": 0.00015775884006074653, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1080, \"end\": 1092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.6095438488684356, \"rank\": 0.6405710627390101, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 5.157091911814082e-12, \"text\": \"Christian values\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other local and international religious leaders\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 972, \"to\": 992}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's mostanticipated multi-sporting event\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1044}, {\"ngram\": \"some claim\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1062}, {\"ngram\": \"a mockery\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"a declaration\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"war\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening, hosted in Paris, France, generated claims that one scene formed by actors, including drag queens, was an obvious mockery of Leonardo Da Vinci's famous painting of The Last Supper.\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1163, \"end\": 1168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.533589864945494e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5558130447646452, \"rank\": 0.7990755260262529, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1277, \"end\": 1285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3882735137241792e-19, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 1286, \"end\": 1294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7164382761710016e-29, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening\", \"from\": 1140, \"to\": 1151}, {\"ngram\": \"one scene\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1209}, {\"ngram\": \"actors\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1226}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"an obvious mockery\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many have also claimed that the ceremony depicted the horseman of death, of the Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse.\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1413, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Four_Horsemen_of_the_Apocalypse\", \"score\": 0.9999999970555109, \"rank\": 2.9443456574422973e-09, \"text\": \"Four Horsemen\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Four_Horsemen_of_the_Apocalypse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Four_Horsemen_of_the_Apocalypse\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1373}, {\"ngram\": \"the horseman\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1404}, {\"ngram\": \"the Apocalypse\", \"from\": 1430, \"to\": 1444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony has been defended as drawing from European history, with the controversial tableau being clarified as a depiction of scenes around the Greek god, Dionysus.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1494, \"end\": 1510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Europe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8652674780646986e-16, \"text\": \"European history\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Europe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Europe\"}, {\"begin\": 1595, \"end\": 1600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9957864918316888, \"rank\": 0.003983591455247247, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1606, \"end\": 1614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0632148723026155e-20, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ceremony\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1459}, {\"ngram\": \"the controversial tableau\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1542}, {\"ngram\": \"a depiction\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1573}, {\"ngram\": \"scenes\", \"from\": 1577, \"to\": 1583}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking at Sunday's mass at the Cathedral of the Immaculate Conception in Port of Spain, the Archbishop said the Olympics were supposed to 'display the cultural values of a civilisation'.\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1700, \"end\": 1705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9667833390156566, \"rank\": 0.029435134831483856, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}, {\"begin\": 1711, \"end\": 1721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9997825331172286, \"rank\": 0.00015775884006074653, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sunday's mass\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1642}, {\"ngram\": \"the Cathedral\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1659}, {\"ngram\": \"the Immaculate Conception\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1688}, {\"ngram\": \"Port\", \"from\": 1692, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1727, \"to\": 1739}, {\"ngram\": \"the cultural values\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1785}, {\"ngram\": \"a civilisation\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1803}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gordon said the Olympic Games were also 'supposed to be that one place where all people are welcome and all people are held together in harmony'.\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1952, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1807, \"end\": 1813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.9999993142889785, \"rank\": 4.651687596632641e-07, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1836}, {\"ngram\": \"that one place\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1877}, {\"ngram\": \"all people\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 1894}, {\"ngram\": \"all people\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1921}, {\"ngram\": \"harmony\", \"from\": 1943, \"to\": 1950}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'It is supposed to be an apolitical place, where there is neutrality and a place where there is a welcome to all people and all cultures.\", \"from\": 1953, \"to\": 2090, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an apolitical place\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 1994}, {\"ngram\": \"neutrality\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2021}, {\"ngram\": \"a place\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2033}, {\"ngram\": \"a welcome\", \"from\": 2049, \"to\": 2058}, {\"ngram\": \"all people\", \"from\": 2062, \"to\": 2072}, {\"ngram\": \"all cultures\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2089}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every time there is an Olympics, you see the cultural creativity of that nation coming to the fore,' he stated.\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an Olympics\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2122}, {\"ngram\": \"the cultural creativity\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2155}, {\"ngram\": \"that nation\", \"from\": 2159, \"to\": 2170}, {\"ngram\": \"the fore\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tableau parody Gordon went on to state that the opening ceremony would usually feature 'artistry like you do not see anywhere else'.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2204, \"end\": 2211, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tableau_vivant\", \"score\": 0.999999999947704, \"rank\": 3.5460686994713814e-11, \"text\": \"Tableau\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tableau_vivant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tableau_vivant\"}, {\"begin\": 2220, \"end\": 2226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.9999993142889785, \"rank\": 4.651687596632641e-07, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2248, \"to\": 2268}, {\"ngram\": \"artistry\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He said all of that was true of the Paris Olympics, which showed artistry 'in ways that were mind-blowing, as only the French can do'.\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2458, \"end\": 2464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9957152595972056, \"rank\": 0.004291249071074644, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2389}, {\"ngram\": \"artistry\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2412}, {\"ngram\": \"ways\", \"from\": 2417, \"to\": 2421}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'And then in the midst of this, they had this tableau, which was clearly a depiction of Da Vinci's Last Supper, with drag queens and the like parading as The Last Supper and that was a parody,' Gordon said.\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2563, \"end\": 2571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7164382761710016e-29, \"text\": \"Da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 2669, \"end\": 2675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.9999993142889785, \"rank\": 4.651687596632641e-07, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the midst\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2497}, {\"ngram\": \"this tableau\", \"from\": 2516, \"to\": 2528}, {\"ngram\": \"a depiction\", \"from\": 2548, \"to\": 2559}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2603}, {\"ngram\": \"the like parading\", \"from\": 2608, \"to\": 2625}, {\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper\", \"from\": 2629, \"to\": 2644}, {\"ngram\": \"a parody\", \"from\": 2658, \"to\": 2666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Archbishop noted the context of The Last Supper, which was that 'Jesus was about to be taken to be whipped, to be mocked, to be handed over, ridiculed and to be given over'.\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2860, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2687, \"end\": 2697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"score\": 0.9997825331172286, \"rank\": 0.00015775884006074653, \"text\": \"Archbishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Archbishop\"}, {\"begin\": 2752, \"end\": 2757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.999999984477654, \"rank\": 1.5522522442244755e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the context\", \"from\": 2704, \"to\": 2715}, {\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper\", \"from\": 2719, \"to\": 2734}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'That is the context of The Last Supper and that context is back with us today,' Gordon said.\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 2955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2943, \"end\": 2949, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.9999993142889785, \"rank\": 4.651687596632641e-07, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the context\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 2882}, {\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper\", \"from\": 2886, \"to\": 2901}, {\"ngram\": \"that context\", \"from\": 2906, \"to\": 2918}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2932, \"to\": 2934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He went on to question whether today's culture was against Christianity, stating that his grandparents' generation 'lived in a culture that could have assumed Christianity as the foundation of the culture'.\", \"from\": 2957, \"to\": 3163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.6095438488684356, \"rank\": 0.6405710627390101, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 3116, \"end\": 3128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.6095438488684356, \"rank\": 0.6405710627390101, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"today's culture\", \"from\": 2988, \"to\": 3003}, {\"ngram\": \"his grandparents' generation\", \"from\": 3043, \"to\": 3071}, {\"ngram\": \"a culture\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3091}, {\"ngram\": \"the foundation\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3146}, {\"ngram\": \"the culture\", \"from\": 3150, \"to\": 3161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Today, we are living in a culture where we can assume that the culture is against the Christian tradition,' Gordon stated, adding: 'When you make fun of a billion people in an Olympics, when you ridicule what is most sacred to them in an Olympics, there is something fundamentally wrong.'\", \"from\": 3165, \"to\": 3454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3252, \"end\": 3261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9991403755832793, \"rank\": 0.0008603640067023825, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 3274, \"end\": 3280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"score\": 0.9999993142889785, \"rank\": 4.651687596632641e-07, \"text\": \"Gordon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Gordon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a culture\", \"from\": 3190, \"to\": 3199}, {\"ngram\": \"the culture\", \"from\": 3225, \"to\": 3236}, {\"ngram\": \"fun\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3315}, {\"ngram\": \"a billion people\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3335}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympics\", \"from\": 3339, \"to\": 3350}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympics\", \"from\": 3401, \"to\": 3412}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 3423, \"to\": 3432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Seventh-Day Adventist Pastor Clive Dottin also spoke against the opening ceremony, stating in a Facebook post on Sunday: 'You have desecrated the painting of The Last Supper, you have staged a blasphemous mockery of Jesus Christ and his disciples.\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3673, \"end\": 3685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.9999999894057511, \"rank\": 1.0594409148067646e-08, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Seventh-Day Adventist Pastor Clive Dottin\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3497}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 3517, \"to\": 3537}, {\"ngram\": \"a Facebook post\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3565}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3575}, {\"ngram\": \"the painting\", \"from\": 3598, \"to\": 3610}, {\"ngram\": \"The Last Supper\", \"from\": 3614, \"to\": 3629}, {\"ngram\": \"a blasphemous mockery\", \"from\": 3647, \"to\": 3668}, {\"ngram\": \"his disciples\", \"from\": 3689,